Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.57,0:02:34.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that I can't play well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.09,0:02:35.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,It's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.60,0:02:38.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.44,0:02:48.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You have your wallet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:49.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.35,0:02:50.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Identification tag?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:50.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:51.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.65,0:02:52.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:52.96,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Tissues?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.96,0:02:53.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:54.18,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Map?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.18,0:02:54.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.87,0:02:55.49,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Compass?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.49,0:02:56.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.22,0:02:57.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Travel provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.35,0:02:57.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:02:58.90,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Helmet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:02:59.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:00.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Handgun? {Pistol? i don't know if there's a difference: http://jisho.org/words?jap=kenjyuu&eng=&dict=edict}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:01.21,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.21,0:03:02.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Hand grenades?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:03.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.14,0:03:04.13,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.29,0:03:07.21,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,She's only joking, Kana-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.88,0:03:10.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What?  You really startled me, sheesh... {nanda, bikkurishimasta yo, mou~ literally, what? you scared me, :female sound of annoyance:}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.45,0:03:12.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd just thought logically, you would've picked up on it quickly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.13,0:03:16.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's mean, Rio-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.19,0:03:21.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,The two of you have been getting along quite well recently, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:25.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Rio's just like an anxious mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.94,0:03:29.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, here's the list for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.33,0:03:31.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening? {Got it? or Listen up! are also ok...ii ka? is the japanese}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.09,0:03:36.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Your mission for today is to go into town and purchase the goods on that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.83,0:03:37.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:38.11,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.49,0:03:41.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,All right, drive safely and have a good trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:42.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.50,0:03:46.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Departing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:52.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:55.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,We're having Pot au Feu for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Detours aren't allowed, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.65,0:03:57.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Alt,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She's{\i0} just like a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:04.67,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,This is a first, isn't it, Noel-chan? {literally, first time, not a first}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.67,0:04:06.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us haven't gone into town together like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:07.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.77,0:04:12.94,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But even saying that, this is pretty much my first time going into town at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:13.51,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:17.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.06,0:04:20.25,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I wonder what that could be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.93,0:04:26.66,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,This is completely different from during the festival, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:30.05,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a calm, quiet town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:41.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:44.81,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,The first was a chimera, a roof ornament special to Trois.{The first one was a nue ? if so, it's a Japanese chimera, mythical creature with a monkey's head, tanuki's body, tiger's limbs, and a snake tail according to my dictionary. jisho.org is down so i can't link/search x.x SO FRUSTRATING}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:47.16,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Designed to ward against evil spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.67,0:04:55.23,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,After that was a drinking fountain, modeled after the twelfth Helvetian Archduke, Akira Arcadia II.{model ni natteiru no ha helvetia no jyuunidai taikou akira arcadia ni sei}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:00.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.41,0:05:04.23,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!  You meant the earlier stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:04.79,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.79,0:05:06.74,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Had to drive safely, since I was instructed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.54,0:05:08.49,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.49,0:05:09.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:12.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan, you're really knowledgeable, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:13.53,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.40,0:05:21.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you coming in or not?  Could you possibly make up your minds?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.77,0:05:22.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,You're obstructing business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:29.04,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,The auntie from the festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.04,0:05:30.79,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,S-i-s-t-e-r. {onee-san versus oba-san}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.27,0:05:33.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't... force people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:37.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,You're as straight-laced as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:39.74,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Then at least call me "Naomi," okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:42.27,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi...-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.20,0:05:56.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Then the next shipment is next month?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:57.03,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.63,0:06:00.62,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,By the way{chinamini - i'll link you if you'd like when the site comes back up x.x}, that girl, does she know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:03.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.81,0:06:09.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,You girls are still as strange as ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:10.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,even though you're soldiers—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:11.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:12.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.95,0:06:14.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's... about those, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:19.49,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,The first time you were here, you were captivated{infatuated} by those as well, weren't you? {shuushin, drawn in, attached to, maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.98,0:06:21.17,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,You've taken a fancy{liking} to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.17,0:06:22.68,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, yes, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:30.11,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Um... m-may I touch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:30.79,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:42.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,A-flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:49.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fish, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:51.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What's it called?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:53.31,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Um... that's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:54.18,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Not a fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.49,0:06:56.06,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:57.15,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,That's a dolphin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.15,0:07:00.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,A creature which is closer to us humans than to fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:04.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,It's a marine mammal from the time when creatures still lived in the sea. {mada umi ni seibutsu ga ita koro no kaisei honyuurui}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:04.61,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,"In the sea"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.61,0:07:06.24,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It lived in the sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.24,0:07:07.12,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:08.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.61,0:07:09.78,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful. {suteki}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.80,0:07:17.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,That old man... he's pretty good at making things like that, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.43,0:07:21.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,It's because he's a romantic, even though he doesn't look it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:23.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know him, then?  The person who made this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.99,0:07:26.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,On the outskirts of town, there's a big workshop{koubou - studio, workshop}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:29.38,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,All of our glassworks are products from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.24,0:07:33.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to see them being made.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:34.97,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.97,0:07:35.70,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.19,0:07:38.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,We're headed there... now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.26,0:07:43.34,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I see!{woa my last name is in that sign xD~yuuri}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:47.73,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You have them make parts for the {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0} for you at that glass workshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:51.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Right.  Naomi gathers parts from the old era for me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:56.82,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But you really are amazing, aren't you, Noel-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:59.70,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You can fix such a complicated machine like that so quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.70,0:08:00.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,"So quickly"? {sfx for quickly, in a snap, just like that, etc.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:07.93,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,For me, my head's already too full just trying to remember the chords for the signal trumpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.61,0:08:11.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,It's not really... that difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:12.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.05,0:08:16.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,'cause machines don't betray.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:19.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:20.16,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,There we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.52,0:08:22.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,Your change is 2,750,000 yen! {2750000 ni hyaku nana jyuu go man en}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:25.51,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  We can get that much back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.51,0:08:26.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.39,0:08:27.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong. {incorrect}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:29.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,The change is 2 yen and 75 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:32.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,{You never change, do you,}Still no sense of humor, huh, Noel-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:34.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:36.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.21,0:08:39.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,The morning trumpet calls recently... is that you, little missy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.31,0:08:41.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:43.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for still being so terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:45.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.63,0:08:47.29,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.29,0:08:50.13,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Storekeeper,0000,0000,0000,,How to say this... it really wakes you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:55.96,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Stare... {sfx for staring...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:02.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking how I need to hurry up and get better so I stop being such a burden to the citizens...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:13.12,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair, Seiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:16.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,Then chase after me and fix it! {if it's unfair, then chase after me}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:20.15,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.15,0:09:21.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sor—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:16.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Alt,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, I also... {she uses boku?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.72,0:09:25.18,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Ha, you hit someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:26.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:29.48,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?  You two are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.01,0:09:32.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,The one from the festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.01,0:09:32.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Alt,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,The clumsy girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:36.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.33,0:09:38.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have made a full recovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.65,0:09:52.78,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,You murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:58.34,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Seiya-san, I'm sure these people have nothing to do with your parents!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.34,0:09:59.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,They're all the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.71,0:10:01.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,I hate soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.71,0:10:03.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and get out of this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:07.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Seiya,0000,0000,0000,,Every morning, with your horrible trumpet playing — it's so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:10.89,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Seiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:13.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really very sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:14.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,He was so rude...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:16.03,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.03,0:10:18.91,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,That boy... he's a war orphan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:21.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, any time he sees a soldier, he indiscriminately...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.79,0:10:24.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.45,0:10:26.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.02,0:10:29.91,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,The truth remains that we're soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:32.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,So that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:34.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.39,0:10:38.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{eyecatch}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:09.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0025,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:11.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0025,,We are soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:16.66,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0025,,When I joined{I was appointed}... I properly recited the Oath of Parador{Paradour? i didn't google this...},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.66,0:11:18.78,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0025,,and I thought I understood what that meant but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.02,0:11:23.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, what am I saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.22,0:11:25.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's something I've always understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:27.78,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,There's no use getting all wishy-washy about it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:31.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:35.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get better to be ready just in case something actually does happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.47,0:11:38.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Without the signal trumpet, everyone would be in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.87,0:11:39.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:40.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.66,0:11:43.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.79,0:11:45.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's the glass workshop?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.56,0:11:46.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.20,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing, Noel-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.20,0:11:51.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,This is my first time ever seeing such a big building!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.45,0:12:12.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This one's no good either, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.96,0:12:15.06,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Is the problem the{TLC -optical? it looks like a lens. he doesn't say it, he just says aberration, but that wouldn't make sense here without another word} aberration?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.06,0:12:17.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The refraction should definitely be right, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.24,0:12:28.74,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm the new recruit, Sorami Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.74,0:12:30.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to meet all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.36,0:12:31.42,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.29,0:12:34.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And um, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.35,0:12:34.93,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:35.28,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:38.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,How was the timing before it started spitting out errors? {hajikidasu}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.23,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Since our last attempt, there were barely any changes in seek time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:44.48,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,In comparison, the distortion of the image sensor has been slightly reduced— {satsuzouzoshi no heien no yogami ha zenkai ni kuraberu to jyakanchi osokunatta***12:41 ask koki}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.44,0:12:44.48,SoRaNoWoTo-Alt,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:49.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to work-related things, the boss just can't focus on other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:53.54,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,But he really is amazing, Old Man Carl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.41,0:13:00.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,He's one of only five outstanding artisans in the country that holds a Meister title.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.09,0:13:05.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,He even won a competition at the capital once and got to present his work to the Archduke!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:10.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Maria!  If you're free enough to be talking, move those hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:13.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!  Sorry, boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:17.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,A title like Meister doesn't fit me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.37,0:13:20.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even hold a candle to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.43,0:13:22.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:25.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,The lens of the {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0}'s optic sensor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.36,0:13:26.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:27.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,That's the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:33.66,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,In order to repair the {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0}, two of the same are needed, so I've asked him to duplicate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:35.66,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,However, it's not going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:37.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they look so pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.72,0:13:41.25,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Besides the main component of silicon dioxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:45.38,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,the lens also {http://jisho.org/words?jap=%E6%B7%B7%E5%85%A5&eng=&dict=edict, mixed in}has some lesser quantities of sodium oxide and magnesium oxide mixed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:48.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,These components rectify{adjust for} the chromatic and spherical aberrations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,in other words, the things which distort the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.07,0:13:54.73,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't know the proportions for those components...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:14:00.48,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,It's because this is like a product created by a magic-like technology of a previous era. {kyuujidai no mahou mitai na gijutsu no sanbutsu dakara na. wow that english sucks.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:09.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I thought glass was just pretty, but it's also complex{muzukashii - difficult, etc.}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:16.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the fact that high-quality materials can be gathered{seize de ha ryoushitsu na keisa? ga saishuu dekiru koto kara} in Seize,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.76,0:14:20.57,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,many small factories that specialized in handicrafts dotted the city. {kougeihin wo chuushin to shita chiisana koubou ga tenzai shiteita.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.38,0:14:24.42,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,This workshop was also originally one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:30.97,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,But when the war became more intense, glass products needed by the military increased,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:35.31,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,and this workshop grew due to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:52.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, I like machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:53.20,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.70,0:14:57.25,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,However, there are instances where machines hurt people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:02.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0} has surely killed many people in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:11.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you would consider a machine that has killed people in the past frightening?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.44,0:15:14.21,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:23.23,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Still, perhaps what's more scary isn't the machine itself, but the people who used it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:27.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, even this trumpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:32.70,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,When I play it, it's terrible, but when Rio-senpai plays it, it sings beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.74,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that a tank is the same way! {kanata ;_; <3; AGREE PLUS. GAWWW. ~Sumi}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:43.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And also, just a little while ago, Rio-senpai let me hear one of the {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0}'s songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.46,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She's able to sing so beautifully!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.93,0:16:03.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she's a good tank!  The {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0} is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.36,0:16:13.21,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I know!  How about next time— {what. x.x}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:21.67,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:24.42,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Let her rest, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:29.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she pulled another all-nighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.71,0:16:35.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan is really working her hardest in order to fix the {\i1}Takemikazuchi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:36.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:39.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,That little lady's a real artisan. {shokunin - worker, mechanic, artisan, craftsman. same word is used to describe carl above - one of only five amazing ___ in the country. whichever one you pick, let's use the same one!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.29,0:16:44.94,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,If she weren't, I wouldn't have accepted the job of making something this annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:49.18,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Here, cover her with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.18,0:16:51.06,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.06,0:16:55.54,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, you guys stopped by Windmill right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.54,0:16:57.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Is Naomi-san doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.20,0:16:59.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.44,0:17:03.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She said your boss is a wonderful romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:05.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,You hear that? {da sou desu yo. da sou is what you add to the of sentences to let others know that what's being said isn't first hand knowledge - you heard it from somewhere. so literally here it's like, that's how it goes, or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.14,0:17:07.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that just great, boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.33,0:17:08.82,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,S-Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.82,0:17:11.08,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and get your ass to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.50,0:17:13.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I made him angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.72,0:17:15.11,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Time for work, time for work!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:26.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But the technology from the past, is it really that amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:27.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Marina,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.57,0:17:32.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Marina,0000,0000,0000,,But the boss always says,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:39.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Marina,0000,0000,0000,,"No matter how amazing it is, in the end, if it was created by humans like us, it {\i1}must{\i0} be reproducible!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:42.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Marina,0000,0000,0000,,You agree, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.02,0:17:42.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:45.16,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Or, well... "yes" is what I'd like to say, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:52.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:57.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Your trumpet playing compared to Rio-san's is truly quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:58.80,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm constantly dwelling on it. {nayamu - worried about, troubled about, etc.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:18:01.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do in order to become more like her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:05.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I have every intention of working as hard as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.35,0:18:08.98,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Look, my lips have swollen this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:11.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:16.70,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times I try, I can never manage to play a sound like her's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:20.41,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I really don't have any talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:21.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Missy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.26,0:18:21.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.24,0:18:26.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,The worst excuse given by those who quit is "having no talent." {Talent tte no ha akirameru yatsu no saitei no iiwake da.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.69,0:18:27.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Give that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.51,0:18:30.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really understand trumpets, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:37.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I do know of a mistake that young people often make.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.47,0:18:40.93,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Missy, aren't you trying to {\i1}force{\i0} the sounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.11,0:19:14.68,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not trying to create this particular shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.68,0:19:18.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,The glass itself wants to become this shape, you see? {awwww}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:29.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much, Uncle Carl! {carl oji-san}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:02.38,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,To allow the sounds to resonate as {\i1}they{\i0} wish{it's hibikitai but perhaps play would be better?}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:18.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{why is she on a protruding rock cliff face x.x}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.06,0:20:51.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:57.31,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Maria,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.  Somehow it seems like the sun rose a step early just for her.{nandaka ano ko dake hitoashi saki ni ohisama ga nobotta mitai yo}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:21:00.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,That little lady's an artisan {shokunin}in her own right, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:01.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Those are some good sounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.94,0:21:03.82,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,"Sounds"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:11.95,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on the amount and types of impurities,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.96,0:21:15.58,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,the sound of glass changes by just the smallest, most delicate degree. {glass ha fukumareru fujyunbutsu no ryou shurui ni yotte goku bimyou ni oto ga kawaru.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:18.75,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,However, even if our ears can't tell the difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.76,0:21:22.34,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,someone with a keen sense of hearing should be able to tell them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:28.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Kanata find the one with the closest sound out of the samples we've created thus far. {kanata ni ha ima made tsukutta sample kara ichiban chikai oto no mono wo sagashite morau}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:30.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,And so, that one would probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:35.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Carl,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, listen to their voices, missy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.10,0:21:36.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:59.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Noel-chan... she's certainly changed since she came here, hasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.93,0:22:01.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.02,0:22:01.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.76,0:22:25.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.02,0:22:26.53,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Noel-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.52,0:22:32.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
